            <h2><a href="http://blog.netbsd.org/tnf/entry/libcxxrt_c_runtime_now_available">libcxxrt C++ runtime now available under BSD license</a></h2><BR>
<div class="descr">May 30, 2011 posted by <i>S.P.Zeidler</I></div><BR>

  <p>The FreeBSD Foundation and the NetBSD Foundation have acquired a non-exclusive copyright license to the libcxxrt C++ runtime software from PathScale, a leader in high performance Fortran, C, and C++ compiler products for AMD64, Intel64, and MIPS. This software is an implementation of the C++ Application Binary Interface originally developed for Itanium and now used for the x86 family by BSD operating systems. Libcxxrt will be available under the 2-clause BSD license.</p>

<p>Read the <a href="http://www.netbsd.org/foundation/press/libcxxrt2011.html">press release</a> for details.</p>

   [<a href="http://blog.netbsd.org/tnf/entry/libcxxrt_c_runtime_now_available#comments">1 comment</a>]
 
</p>


