            <h2><a href="http://blog.netbsd.org/tnf/entry/interview_with_a_netbsd_developer">Interview with a NetBSD developer: today, Amitai Schlair, aka schmonz@</a></h2><BR>
<div class="descr">December 08, 2010 posted by <i>Guillaume Lasmayous</I></div><BR>

  A few months after Thomas Klausner's interview, please welcome today Amitai, better known as schmonz@.

<pre>
<strong>NetBSDfr: For those of our readers that don't know you, can you introduce
yourself briefly ?</strong><br/>
I grew up in a suburb of Chicago. Both at school and at home, my
childhood computing skewed Appleward. The exception was Texas
Instruments graphing calculators. By the end of high school, I had a
nearly complete set.
</pre>
<p>
[<a class="readmore" href="http://blog.netbsd.org/tnf/entry/interview_with_a_netbsd_developer">Read More</a>]

